{
  "text": "A second example of negative representational bias can be found in the work by Igel and Stagge [CITATION_1] . They show that when dealing with redundant encodings, operators that are unbiased in genotype space may exhibit a remarkable bias in phenotype [CITATION_2] Assuming that the nodes of a completely connected, undirected graph G = (V; E) are labeled from 1 to jV j, a Pr\u00fcfer number is a string of length jV j 0 2 of node labels that encodes one of the possible spanning trees of G. There is a one-to-one mapping between the possible Pr\u00fcfer numbers and the spanning trees of a graph.",
